2007-05-17  Tomas Cerha  <cerha@brailcom.org>

	* pytis/form/_grid.py: Don't create just another `PresentedRow'
	instance for the ListTable but share the form's instance.

	* pytis/data/types_.py (Binary.Buffer.load): Allow passing the
	original filename.

	* pytis/form/inputfield.py: Removed forgotten print.  Call
	`_on_change' also for text fields manually.  Pass the original
	filename of file data.

	* pytis/form/form.py: Use the new command handling mechanism.
	Always report the ShowForm unchanged.  Allow overriding the
	singleline argument for the created `PresentedRow' instance.
	(ShowFoem): Avoid unwanted computer invocations on initialization.

	* pytis/form/list.py: Use the new command handling mechanism.
	Create the PresentedRow instance as singleline and pass it to
	`ListTable'.  Avoid unwanted computer invocations on PresentedRow
	initialization.

	* pytis/form/application.py: Detect dual forms in startup_forms
	automatically.

	* pytis/presentation/field.py: Save the original_row before
	executing the initial computers.  Allow passing validation
	arguments.  Always recreate the stored data row to make sure it
	has all the needed columns.  Minor improvements.  Make sure the
	order of fields in the data row corresponds to the order of field
	specifications.

	* pytis/presentation/_test.py: Test it.

2007-05-16  Tomas Cerha  <cerha@brailcom.org>

	* pytis/presentation/field.py: Compute dirty values when saving
	the original row.  Added support for validation and keeping track
	invalid user input values.

	* pytis/presentation/_test.py: New tests.

	* pytis/form/_grid.py: Don't duplicate things now implemented in
	PresentedRow.

	* pytis/form/list.py: Updated for the changed cell editor and
	`EditedRow' interface.

	* pytis/form/inputfield.py: Major cleanup, improvements and a few
	bugfixes.

	* pytis/form/form.py: Fixed a problem with transactions and
	multiple uses of PopupEdit.  Updated for the changed interface of
	input fields.  Inserted row initialization fixed.

2007-05-15  Tomas Cerha  <cerha@brailcom.org>

	* pytis/form/search.py: Updated (fixed) for the new dialog creation strategy.

	* pytis/form/inputfield.py (ImageField._disable): Stupid bug fixed.

